Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Sure, one way to get around the autoindex problem is to delete the document that uses it, but I'd like an explanation of why we don't want this document any more: https://docs.openstack.org/glance/latest/contributor/modules.html

Patch Set 3:

My 2 cents on that are here - http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-March/128653.html

Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

I agree on the fact that it should be explained at least in the commit message that we are dropping this.

Patch Set 3:

(1 comment)
Patch Set 4: Commit message was updated.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(1) There's a difference between "limited use" and "no use".   (2) I don't like seeing this slip by as part of an unrelated change.  According to http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-March/128594.html , there is a workaround to the pbr autoindex feature.  I'd like you to try that.

@Nguyen: I appreciate your taking on this task, please don't take my opposition personally.

I don't think the point of the new PTI was to force us to drop some content from our docs, so I'd prefer to see us not have to do that.

Patch Set 4:

Thanks, will find out a better solution.
